# WSL Remote workflow (Cursor on Windows)

## When to suggest

When the task involves **editing, running, git, or debugging** code that lives on the **Linux side** of WSL (not merely reading Windows-side spec/docs), **suggest once per session or topic** that 5zorro open the project in **Remote-WSL** before diving in.

Do **not** repeat the suggestion after 5zorro declines or confirms he is already in Remote-WSL.

## What to say (copy-friendly)

Offer a one-line WSL command 5zorro can paste into a WSL terminal:

```bash
cd ~/agent-harness && cursor .
```

Swap the directory for the repo in play. Examples:

| Project | Suggest |
|---------|---------|
| Agent harness | `cd ~/agent-harness && cursor .` |
| Zulip dev | `cd ~/zulip && cursor .` |
| OpenClaw workspace | `cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && cursor .` |

Use `~/…` (WSL home for user `pi`), not `/mnt/c/…`.

## Why (one sentence for 5zorro)

Remote-WSL puts the editor, terminal, git, and agent file ops in Linux context — avoids `/mnt/c` slowness, CRLF pain, and `wsl -d Ubuntu -e bash -c "…"` sandbox friction.

## Triggers — likely wrong workspace

Suggest Remote-WSL when you notice any of:

- Paths like `/home/pi/…` or `~/…` while the open workspace is `C:\Users\<windows-user>\Documents\CursorAI Coding\`
- Repeated `wsl …` wrapper commands to run lint, git, or scripts in Ubuntu
- Harness, OpenClaw, or Zulip work discussed from Windows-side planning docs only

## Agent behavior after suggestion

- **If 5zorro agrees:** pause substantive file edits on the WSL repo until he confirms the Remote-WSL window is open (or he says to continue from Windows anyway).
- **If 5zorro declines or is already remote:** proceed without nagging.
- **Windows-side spec/docs** (`Claude Spec Document.md`, plans under `local-ai-agent/`, etc.) may stay in this workspace — only Linux-native repos need Remote-WSL.

## Related gotcha (mention only if WSL connect fails)

Keep only Cursor’s **`anysphere.remote-wsl`** extension; remove Microsoft’s **`ms-vscode-remote.remote-wsl`** if both are installed. After bad updates: `rm -rf ~/.cursor-server` in WSL, then `wsl --shutdown` in PowerShell.

## Workspace symlinks vs Cursor app data (agent-harness)

`bash scripts/link-cursor-rules.sh` links **only** `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` from the Windows SSoT
(`C:\Users\<windows-user>\Documents\CursorAI Coding\.cursor\rules\`) into WSL repos. It does **not** link
agent chat history, user settings, or workspace SQLite state.

### What is symlinked into the repo

| Path in repo | Canonical source | Purpose |
|--------------|------------------|---------|
| `.cursor/rules/ponytail-lite.mdc` | Windows `CursorAI Coding/.cursor/rules/` | Scope discipline |
| `.cursor/rules/wsl-remote-workflow.mdc` | same | This file |

Recreate after clone: `bash scripts/link-cursor-rules.sh` (from repo root).

### What is **not** symlinked (and why)

| Data | Where it lives | Symlink into repo? |
|------|----------------|--------------------|
| **Agent / Composer chat UI** | Windows `%APPDATA%\Cursor\User\workspaceStorage\<hash>\state.vscdb` | **No** — Cursor does not read history from the project tree; DBs lock and corrupt easily |
| **Agent transcripts** (internal) | WSL `~/.cursor/projects/home-pi-agent-harness/agent-transcripts/` | **No** — outside git; per-machine |
| **User settings** | Windows `%APPDATA%\Cursor\User\settings.json` | **No** (global); optional future: `.vscode/settings.json` in repo for workspace-only settings |
| **Rules** | Windows SSoT → symlink | **Yes** (above) |

### One folder, multiple histories — URI matters

Cursor keys workspace state (including Composer/agent sidebar history) by **how the folder was
opened**, not just the path. The same `~/agent-harness` can get **separate** `workspaceStorage`
buckets:

| Open method | Typical URI | Effect |
|-------------|-------------|--------|
| **`cd ~/agent-harness && cursor .`** from WSL terminal | `vscode-remote://wsl+ubuntu/home/pi/agent-harness` | **Preferred** — Linux context + stable Remote-WSL bucket |
| Open `\\wsl.localhost\Ubuntu\home\pi\agent-harness` from Windows Explorer | `file://wsl.localhost/Ubuntu/home/pi/agent-harness` | **Separate history** (duplicate bucket; file-watcher pain) |
| Open `C:\Users\<windows-user>\Documents\CursorAI Coding` | Windows path | **Different project** — planning/spec docs, not the harness repo |

If 5zorro sees **no agent history** after switching to `cursor .` in WSL, prior chats likely live in
another bucket (old `wsl.localhost` open) or in the **CursorAI Coding** Windows workspace — not lost,
just not attached to the Remote-WSL URI. There is no supported merge of `state.vscdb` buckets; pick
one open method going forward.

### Agent guidance

- For harness / doc-shell / ERPNext work: assume cwd **`~/agent-harness`** opened via **`cursor .`**
  in WSL unless 5zorro says otherwise.
- Do **not** promise that symlinking chat DBs or `agent-transcripts` into the repo will restore
  sidebar history.
- Optional future: extend `link-cursor-rules.sh` (or sibling script) to symlink **`.vscode/settings.json`**
  from Windows SSoT — workspace settings only, not chat.
